issue_body:
RLIKE operator, with a case insensitive regex (eg. `(?i)foo`) behaves differently when being folded compared to normal execution.

In particular, the case insensitive prefix `(?i)` is considered and used only when the expression can be folded

Schema:
```
POST /test
{
    "mappings": {
        "properties":{
            "action": {
                "type":"keyword"
            }
        }
    }
}


```

```
PUT test/_doc/1
{
  "action": "StopInstance"
}
```


Normal regex query: returns the record as expected

```
POST /_query
{
  "query": """
FROM rlike_test 
| WHERE action RLIKE "Stop.*"
  """
}
```

Query with case insensitive syntax `(?i)`: returns nothing

```
POST /_query
{
  "query": """
FROM rlike_test 
| WHERE action RLIKE "(?i)Stop.*"
  """
}
```


Query with ROW (folded expression) and case insensitive syntax `(?i)`: returns one record

```
POST /_query
{
  "query": """
ROW action = "StopInstance"
| WHERE action RLIKE "(?i)Stop.*"
  """
}
```
